1 AN ACT
2 To enact Part IV of Chapter 30 of Title 3 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950, to be
3 comprised of R.S. 3:4748.1 through 4748.4, relative to cell cultured food products;
4 to prohibit the sale of cell cultured food products for human consumption; to provide
5 for penalties; to provide for rules and regulations; and to provide for related matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. Part IV of Chapter 30 of Title 3 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950,
8 comprised of R.S. 3:4748.1 through 4748.4, is hereby enacted to read as follows:
9 PART IV. CELL CULTURED FOOD PRODUCTS
10 §4748.1. Short title
11 This Part shall be known and may be cited as the "Cell Cultured Food
12 Products Act".
13 §4748.2. Cell cultured food products; prohibition
14 A. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, no person
15 shall advertise, manufacture, distribute, sell, or offer for sale, any cell cultured
16 food product for human consumption in this state.
17 B. For purposes of this Part, cell cultured food product means any
